						               													<description>Wargame Japanese History game #27.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game uses a worker-placement system and abstractly covers the period from the start of the Mibu R&amp;#197;&amp;#141;shigumi (1863) to the end of the Boshin War (1869).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In start, only mild preparing missions can be conducted such as recruiting, financing, connection making.  Then, each turn a new mission is revealed and can be selected. The most VPs are awarded for assassination of enemy roushi and/or success of military campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends after 5 or 6 turns. It can be played with 2,3 or 4 players and within 2 hours.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Mibu R&amp;#197;&amp;#141;shigumi (&amp;#229;&amp;#163;&amp;#172;&amp;#231;&amp;#148;&amp;#159;&amp;#231;&amp;#139;&amp;#188;&amp;#233;&amp;#161;&amp;#155;&amp;#230;&amp;#156;&amp;#171;&amp;#232;&amp;#168;&amp;#152;) was a police unit formed from many samurais in 1863 to protect the Shogunate government. It was an organization which precede the famous Shinsen Gumi. https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shinsengumi&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
